All Spenser wants to do is get his trucking license, move to Arizona and get the fuck out of Beantown.
And more importantly for some, fans of the star will recognize that he’s found a franchise-friendly character that works for him.
He’s just a man with a heart, a Massachusetts drivers’ license, a mean left hook and a code of honor.
Look what you do get: Wahlberg and Berg proving they can go light for a change.
Stand-up comic Iliza Schlesinger as the movie’s part-time romantic interest/full-time comic relief and a steroidal caricature of a scary Southie woman.